radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung bases are clear. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation without focal lesions. No intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation. The gallbladder is normal without stones. The pancreas shows normal attenuation without focal lesions. The spleen is normal. The adrenal glands are normal in size and shape. The kidneys are normal in size with no stones or lesions. The small bowel is normal. The appendix has hyperenhancing walls, enlarged at 11 mm with mild surrounding fat stranding. No fluid collections. No abdominal aortic aneurysm or lymphadenopathy. Trace free fluid in the pelvis likely physiologic.
